{{Han etym}}
In the {{w|Chu (state)|Chu}} form, a {{Han compound|人|龹|t1=person|ls=psc|c1=s|c2=p|nocap=y}}. In the {{w|Small Seal Script}} form, a {{Han compound|人|卷|t1=person|ls=psc|c1=s|c2=p|nocap=y}}.

===Etymology===
Compare {{cog|bo|ཀྱོར་ཀྱོར||weak; feeble}}, {{cog|bo|ཁྱོར་བ||to stumble; to move totteringly}}, {{cog|bo|འཁྱོར་བ||to stagger, to reel}} ({{zh-ref|Bodman, 1980}}). Cognate with {{och-l|痯|exhausted}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

